quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  2,197,"The Hajj is (in) the well known months. Then whosoever makes it incumbent on himself to perform the Hajj therein, then there is no approaching (your wives), nor transgression nor disputing during the Hajj. And whatever good you do God knows it. And make provision (for yourselves for the journey) but guarding (against evil) is certainly the best provision, and fear Me, O men of understanding"
  2,198,"There is no sin upon you if you seek the grace of your Lord, so when you hasten from Arafat then remember God near the sacred monument and remember Him as He has guided you, though before this you were of those who were astray"
  2,199,"Then hasten on from where people hasten on, and seek protective forgiveness from God, God is certainly Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  2,200,"So when you have completed your devotional rites, then remember God as you remembered (talked about) your fathers or remember Him still more intensely (and reverently). So among human beings are those who say, \"Our Lord ! give us in this world,\" and they have no portion in the hereafter"
  2,201,"And of them are those who say, \"Our Lord ! give us good in this world and good in the hereafter and save us from the punishment of fire"
  2,202,"Those are the persons for whom there is (their) portion of what they earned, and God is Quick at (settling) the account"
  2,203,"And remember God during the numbered days, then whoever hastens on in two days there is no sin on him and whoever delays there is no sin on him, (this is) for him who guards (against evil), and fear God and know that you will be gathered towards Him"
  2,204,"And among human beings is he whose speech about the life of the world makes you wonder, and he makes God witness over that which is in his heart, yet he is the most rigid in opposition"
  2,205,and when he turns back (from you) he strives in the earth to cause corruption in it and to destroy crop and cattle and God does not like corruption
  2,206,"And when it is said to him, \"Fear God,\" the might (pride) makes him hold on to sin, so hell is sufficient for him and it is surely an evil place of habitation"
  2,207,"And among human beings is he who sells himself seeking the pleasure of God, and God is full of pity for (His) servants"
  2,208,"O you who believe ! enter into Islam completely (with total submission) and do not follow the footsteps of the devil, he is certainly an open enemy for you"
  2,209,"But if you slip after clear proofs have come to you then know that God is Mighty, Wise"
  2,210,Do they wait for anything else than that God should come to them in the shadows of the clouds with the angels and the affair be decided? And to God are returned (all) affairs